---
title: Honey Butter–Glazed Beef with Smoky Potato Salad & Roasted Broccoli
description: Pork just loves a sweet sauce, and this simple honey-butter glaze is just the thing for bringing these tender boneless chops to the next level. We’re serving them with a big helping of creamy, tangy potato salad (livened up with zingy mustard and crisp scallions) to bring the cookout vibes, plus a side of roasted salt-and-pepper broccoli to round things out. It’s a meat and potatoes meal that's quick to the table, and quick to satisfy.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66019a2ada283ecbc2883ce8-efb4a679.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6759f19bdaedc2bd1295ae73-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/honey-butter-glazed-beef-6759f19bdaedc2bd1295ae73
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 740 kcal
  fat: 39 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 58 g
  sugar: 22 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 390 mg
course: main course
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
author: HelloFresh
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Cut @broccoli{1} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Drain, then rinse potatoes under cold water; transfer to a #large bowl{} and refrigerate until ready to use.

While potatoes cook, toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with half the @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon} and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> Lower heat to medium if pork is browning too quickly.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken or beef for pork. Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

To bowl with cooled potatoes, add scallion whites, @smoky mustard{1%ounce}, and @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}; stir until thoroughly combined. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Refrigerate until ready to serve.

Return pan used for beef to stovetop over medium heat. Add @honey{4%teaspoon}, @butter{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring, until butter has melted, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Return beef to pan and cook, turning occasionally, until fully coated and glazed, ~{1-2%minutes}. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

> Glaze chicken or beef as instructed.

Thinly slice beef crosswise.

Divide beef, potato salad, and broccoli between plates. Spoon any remaining glaze over beef. Sprinkle scallion greens over potato salad and serve.

> Thinly slice chicken or beef against the grain.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.